default-Does the ECO consider the current levels of non-compliance recorded by HMRC visits as acceptable?
default&#xa0;
default-What is the ECO doing to ensure better compliance levels on the part of licence holders?
default&#xa0;
default-How does the ECO define (i) ‘compliant (ii) generally compliant’ (iii) ‘not fully compliant’ and (iv) non-compliant?
default&#xa0;
default-Can the ECO provide examples of the most serious cases of (i) unlicensed shipments uncovered by visits in the 2007-10 period and (ii) non-compliance uncovered by visits in 2011 and 2012?
default&#xa0;
default-Will the ECO provide data on the number of unlicensed shipments discovered as a result of compliance visits in 2011 and 2012 respectively?
default&#xa0;
default-Will the ECO commit to provide such data in future reports, in line with its more general commitment to transparency?
default&#xa0;
default-Why has there been such a significant drop in (i) the number of overall compliance visits since 2009 and (ii) the number of first time and routine visits in particular?
